				<p><p>That depends on what you mean.  If your question is about output, then the answer is you have 4 degrees of freedom: thrust, pitch, yaw, and roll.  If you question is about the dynamics of the helicopter, then you have to make some assumptions.  Assuming the vehicle is a rigid body is usually a good assumption for answering basic questions about a system, in which case it would have 6 DOF, position in x, y, and z, plus rotation about x, y, and z.  If your question is about inputs, then the answer is also 6 DOF, because you have to measure all 6 DOF if you want to be able to control a quadcopter.  </p>
