				<p><p>I think the term you are looking for is <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Holonomic_(robotics)" rel="nofollow">Holonomic</a>.  The important distinction that you've missed is between "total degrees of freedom" and "controllable degrees of freedom" (which is what most roboticists mean when they refer to DOF).  </p>

<p>Your quadcopter is non-holonomic; it can achieve 6 degrees of freedom, but only by planning maneuvers that make use of its 4 controllable degrees of freedom.  </p>
